%T A394694 2,2,5,1,2,2,4,1,5,1,3,3,2,1,5,2,3,2,3,1,4,2,5,2,2,1,6,1,2,3,4,2,4,1,
%U A394694 3,2,4,1,7,1,2,3,3,2,4,1,5,3,2,1,6,2,2,2,4
%N A394694 Number of occurrences of n in A081493.
%C A394694 Conjecturally: a(n) = A000005(n-1)/2 + e(n), where e(n) = 1/2 if n-1 is a perfect square, 1 if n-1 is pronic, and 0 otherwise.
%C A394694 Here A000005(k) is the number of divisors of k.
%C A394694 In particular, a(n) = 1 for all n of the form p+1 where p is an odd prime (since A000005(p) = 2). Example: a(4) = 1 since 4 = 3 + 1 and 3 is prime.
%C A394694 Also, the number of occurrences of n in A209297 is A033831(n-1) for n >= 2.
%C A394694 Also conjecturally: a(n) + A033831(n-1) = A000005(n-1) for n >= 2.
%C A394694 Equivalently, A033831(n-1) = A000005(n-1)/2 + d(n), where d(n) = -1/2 if n-1 is a perfect square, -1 if n-1 is pronic, and 0 otherwise.
%e A394694 Initial rows of A081493:
%e A394694   1;
%e A394694   2,  3;
%e A394694   3,  5,  7;
%e A394694   4,  7, 10, 13;
%e A394694   5,  9, 13, 17, 21;
%e A394694   6, 11, 16, 21, 26, 31;
%e A394694   7, 13, 19, 25, 31, 37, 43.
%e A394694 The following counts are obtained directly from the above rows:
%e A394694 n = 5: 5 occurs twice, so a(5) = 2. Here n-1 = 4 (square), tau(4) = 3, and (3+1)/2 = 2.
%e A394694 n = 7: 7 occurs three times, so a(7) = 3. Here n-1 = 6 (pronic), tau(6) = 4, and (4+2)/2 = 3.
%e A394694 n = 6: 6 occurs once, so a(6) = 1. Here n-1 = 5, tau(5) = 2, and 2/2 = 1.
%t A394694 a[n_]:=Count[Table[NestList[#+i-1&, i, i-1], {i, n}]//Flatten,n];Array[a,89] (* _James C. McMahon_, Apr 08 2026 *)
%o A394694 (Python)
%o A394694 from collections import defaultdict
%o A394694 def a_list(N):
%o A394694     freq = defaultdict(int)
%o A394694     for n in range(1, N+1):
%o A394694         for k in range(n):
%o A394694             val = n + k*(n-1)
%o A394694             if val <= N:
%o A394694                 freq[val] += 1
%o A394694     return [freq[n] for n in range(1, N+1)]
%o A394694 print(a_list(90))
%Y A394694 Cf. A081493, A033831, A000005, A209297.
%K A394694 nonn,easy
%O A394694 1,3
